Five hundred animals have been intercepted by the Joint Taskforce Operations in Niger following onslaught against terrorists in the State. The Joint Taskforce intercepted the animals at Kuchi and Galadiman- Kogo, Alawa and Erena communities of Munya and Shiroro local governments areas of Niger State. The interception was announced by the Commissioner of Local Government, Chieftaincy Affairs and Internal Security, Emmanuel Umar in Minna.   BREAKING: Family receives corpse of OAU MBA student     Toyota retains its crown as world’s biggest car seller in…     Davido acknowledges benefit of workout sessions   According to him, the recovery includes 300 cows and 100 sheep adding that the animals will under the custody of the Ministry of Livestock. - Advertisement - “The onslaught on bandits is a continuous exercise until the state is rid of all rustlers, kidnapping and other criminal elements.” Umar stated that the security task force has succeeded in neutralizing several bandits but not without casualty on the side of the security agencies. The Commissioner further stated that moves are on to identify the owners of the animals while the others whose owner cannot be found would be auctioned.